allenged in today's internet age. Following a legal analysis of various intellectual property court cases, Jessica Silbey examines the experiences of everyday creators and innovators navigating ownership, sharing, and sustainability within the internet eco-system and current IP laws. Crucially, the book encourages refiguring the substance of "progress" and the function of intellectual property in terms that demonstrate the urgency of art and science to social justice today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aIntellectual propertyzUnited States. 0aTechnology and lawzUnited States. 7aLAW / Intellectual Property / General.2bisacsh  aIntellectual property.  aconstitutional law.  acopyright.  adistributive justice.  aequality.  ainternet.  apatent.  aprecarity.  aprivacy.  atrademark.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363192240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631922/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles